feels.name: Irritation
feels.quote: every little untoward circumstance that befell him, and which indirectly sprang from his luckless mishap, almost invariably irritated or exasperated Ahab.

feels.name: Exasperation
feels.quote: every little untoward circumstance that befell him, and which indirectly sprang from his luckless mishap, almost invariably irritated or exasperated Ahab.

feels.name: Exultation
feels.quote: Aye, aye—they were mine—my irons—cried Ahab, exultingly—but on!

feels.name: Goodhumoredness
feels.quote: Shall I call that wise or foolish, now; if it be really wise it has a foolish look to it; yet, if it be really foolish, then has it a sort of wiseish look to it. But, avast; here comes our old Manxman—the old hearse-driver, he must have been, that is, before he took to the sea.
